# Item Card Layout

All food item cards (`.item-card`) use a consistent layout pattern:

## Structure

Each card contains three elements in order: **graphic**, **name**, **tag** (optional).

```html
<div class="item-card">
  <div class="sa sa-apple"></div>
  <div class="item-name">Apple</div>
  <div class="item-tag tag-fibre">Fibre+</div>
</div>
```

## Positioning Rules

- Cards use `display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center` with a `min-height`
- The graphic (`.sa`) gets `margin-top: auto` to push it **down** away from the top border
- The food name (`.item-name`) gets a fixed `margin-top` (e.g. `6px`) to create consistent spacing between graphic and text
- Name and tag sit at the **bottom** of the card, consistently aligned across all cards regardless of graphic height

```css
.item-card > .sa { margin-top: auto; }
.item-name { margin-top: 6px; }
```

## Key Principle

Graphics float toward the bottom-center of the card. Text anchors at the bottom. The empty space is always **above** the graphic, never between graphic and text.
